groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:name: PR#1 - Kerr Park
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:short_description: This was hidden for my 2011 Fall Picnic. It was part of a Geo Game but remains as a cache.
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:long_description:
Kerr Park is a 45-acre municipal park adjacent to the Brandywine Creek. Centrally located in the Borough of Downingtown, it offers facilities for sports and community events. The park includes picnic pavilions, public restrooms, a trout hatchery and the “Sky’s the Limit Playground”. The cache is located just off the white blazed Brandywine Trail which runs along the Brandywine Creek.
Be careful and have fun!

groundspeak:log.groundspeak:text: Signs of extensive flooding, but the cache is still here. Took us a while to find it with GPS bouncing around, but dawnie22 made the find. 19acassel searched with us too.
